item.description:
arXiv:2606.12046v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: The main purpose of this note is to give a proof of the fact that the Toda brackets \ $\langle ar{
u},\sigma, ar{
u}angle$ and $\langle
u,\eta,  ar{\sigma}angle$ are not trivial. This is an affirmative answer of M.~Mahowald's Conjecture (J. Mukai, Determination of the $P$-image by Toda brackets, Geometry and Topology Monographs 	extbf{13}(2008), 355--383). The second purpose is to determine the relations including $ ar{
u}_6\omega_{14}$ in $\pi^6_{30}$ and $ ar{
u}_7\omega_{15}$ in $\pi^7_{31}$. To this end, we provide relations between the Toda bracket and the $J$-homomorphism, and between the Toda bracket and the generalized $P$-homomorphism.
